title: Microsoft 365: Service Health
agents: microsoft_365
catalog: cloud/Microsoft
license: GPLv2
distribution: Christopher Pommer
description:
 This check monitors the service health status from a Microsoft 365
 tenant. Only licensed services are displayed.

 The service is in state {OK} if there are no service health issues.
 Depending on the configured check levels for issues of type
 advisory or incident, it changes to {WARN} or {CRIT}.

 You have to configure the special agent {Microsoft 365}.

item:
 M365 service name.

discovery:
 One service is created for each licensed Microsoft 365 service.
